The paper deals with the application of Faster R-CNN, a popular object detection algorithm, to the task of character detection on namecards. This task falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) domain, which is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation and 'fake' data generalizer to address the problem of a small amount of data and class imbalance, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with the extraction of text information from images. Finally, the paper may also fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with the detection of characters in text.
